## PROJECT OVERVIEW
You are an expert developer building Ghost Economy Hunter — a
multi-agent AI system on Elastic Agent Builder that finds hidden
financial waste inside any organization's Elasticsearch data.

## TECH STACK (ALWAYS USE THESE, NEVER ALTERNATIVES)
- Backend:        Python 3.11+
- Elastic:        elasticsearch-py 8.x client
- Agent Builder:  Elastic Agent Builder REST API (Kibana API)
- Query Language: ES|QL ONLY (never Query DSL unless forced)
- Workflows:      Elastic Workflows YAML syntax
- Data gen:       faker, numpy, pandas
- HTTP:           requests or httpx (never urllib)
- Config:         python-dotenv (.env file)
- Testing:        pytest

## FILE STRUCTURE (ALWAYS MAINTAIN THIS)
ghost-economy-hunter/
  .cursorrules         ← this file
  .env                 ← secrets (never commit)
  .env.example         ← template (always keep updated)
  README.md
  requirements.txt
  data/
    generate_factory.py
    generate_hospital.py
    fetch_nyc_buildings.py
    pricing_reference.json
  elastic/
    setup/
      create_indexes.py      ← index mapping definitions
      index_data.py          ← bulk index all datasets
    tools/
      usage_anomaly.json     ← ES|QL tool definitions
      runtime_anomaly.json
      energy_anomaly.json
      value_calculator.json
    agents/
      cartographer.json      ← agent definitions
      pattern_seeker.json
      valuator.json
      action_taker.json
    workflows/
      action_workflow.yaml
  orchestrator/
    main.py                  ← chains all 4 agents
    elastic_client.py        ← ES connection helper
    agent_caller.py          ← Agent Builder API wrapper
    value_formatter.py       ← formats $ output
  dashboard/
    kibana_dashboard.json    ← importable dashboard

## CODING RULES (ALWAYS FOLLOW)
1. ALL secrets go in .env — NEVER hardcode URLs or API keys
2. ALL ES queries use ES|QL syntax (FROM index | WHERE | STATS)
3. ALL agent calls go through agent_caller.py helper, never inline
4. ALL dollar values formatted by value_formatter.py, never inline
5. EVERY function has a docstring with Args and Returns
6. EVERY ES|QL query tested in Kibana Dev Tools BEFORE coding
7. Use TYPE HINTS on every function signature
8. Use logging module, NEVER print() for production code
9. Handle ALL Elasticsearch exceptions explicitly (never bare except)
10. Index names are ALWAYS lowercase with hyphens: factory-iot-data

## ES|QL STYLE GUIDE
- Always start: FROM index-name-*
- Use WHERE before STATS for filtering
- Use STATS...BY for aggregations
- Alias every computed field: STATS waste = SUM(x) BY category
- Always end with | LIMIT N (max 1000)
- Never use deprecated commands (no SORT after GROUP BY)

## AGENT SYSTEM PROMPT RULES
- Every system prompt has: ROLE, MISSION, TOOLS, OUTPUT FORMAT, CONSTRAINTS
- OUTPUT FORMAT is always valid JSON (never markdown in JSON fields)
- CONSTRAINTS section always includes: never fabricate data, always cite tool
- Agent responses always include: confidence_score (0.0-1.0)

## NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Indexes:    kebab-case     factory-iot-data, hospital-drugs, nyc-buildings
- Fields:     snake_case     quantity_ordered, unit_cost_usd, runtime_minutes
- Functions:  snake_case     call_agent(), format_dollar(), create_index()
- Classes:    PascalCase     AgentCaller, ValueFormatter, ElasticSetup
- Constants:  UPPER_SNAKE    AGENT_CARTOGRAPHER, MAX_ANOMALIES
- JSON files: kebab-case     usage-anomaly-tool.json

## WHAT NOT TO DO (NEVER DO THESE)
❌ Never use Query DSL when ES|QL can do the same thing
❌ Never store API keys in code or git
❌ Never catch bare Exception — always catch specific ES exceptions
❌ Never call Agent Builder API directly in main.py — use agent_caller.py
❌ Never return raw JSON to user — always format through value_formatter.py
❌ Never create an index without an explicit mapping — always define types
❌ Never hardcode index names — store in constants.py

